+2. Import the Step-3 exact-symmetry taxonomy from exploration-001.
+3. For each candidate, test which ingredients survive true exact symmetries, which only require fixed canonicalization, and which would amount to substantive model drift.
+4. Record whether each candidate's downstream gate remains meaningful after the robustness audit.
+5. Decide whether Chain Step 4 is well-posed and, if not, which negative failure bucket is earned.
