    25	### 1. Stage order
    26	
    27	- Classification: `essential`
    28	- Status: `[VERIFIED]`
    29	- Justification:
    30	  the inherited Atlas reconstruction does not present Tao's mechanism as a
    31	  generic five-node graph. It presents an ordered delayed-abrupt-transfer
    32	  sequence:
    33	  weak pump `X1,n -> X2,n`, tiny seed into `X3,n`, amplification of `X3,n`,
    34	  rotor exchange `X1,n <-> X4,n`, and final transfer `X4,n -> X1,n+1`.
    35	  The final report explicitly calls this the load-bearing mechanism rather than
    36	  a decorative packaging choice. A packet family that scrambles this order is
    37	  no longer Tao-like in the sense the mission inherited.
    38	
    39	### 2. Delayed-threshold behavior
    40	
    41	- Classification: `essential`
    42	- Status: `[VERIFIED]`
    43	- Justification:
    44	  the decisive Tao feature is not merely multistage transfer but delayed
    45	  activation created by exponential amplification of an exponentially tiny
    46	  trigger. The final report names delayed threshold activation as the
    47	  load-bearing mechanism, and the exploration-001 reconstruction makes the
    48	  threshold time `t_c` explicit. Removing the delayed-threshold logic collapses
    49	  the mechanism into an ordinary sparse cascade.
    50	
