+  the anchored local record, following the same operational fallback already
+  recorded in Step 2.
+
+## Audit Method
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Freeze the packet object, interaction core, spectator classes,
+  sign / amplitude / phase sheet, activation window, and downstream gates as
+  stated in Step 1 and Step 2.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Use the Exploration-001 taxonomy:
+  minimal true exact-symmetry tier,
+  frozen canonicalization tier,
+  and substantive model-change tier.
+- `[VERIFIED]` For each candidate, ask:
+  what survives the true-symmetry tier,
+  what depends only on the frozen canonical packet sheet,
+  what would become a different model if changed,
+  and whether the downstream gate still measures a real theorem-facing or
+  construction-facing quantity in one fixed burden currency.
+
+## Candidate Audit
+
+### 1. Template-Defect Near-Closure
+
+- `[INFERRED]` **True-symmetry tier.**
+  No local evidence says the candidate fails under the minimal exact-symmetry
+  tier.
